records.addlTxt:
Defendant Marcus M Thurmon in court, in custody, with attorney Eric Lowenberg for Robert J. Penegor.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Christine Bohn, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:
Withheld Sentence (Credit for 59 days if revoked)
Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	No Use or Possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-           Sign medical release for Agent;
-           Obtain a Valid Driver's License within the first 4 months;
-	Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
-	Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
-            20 Hours Community Service per year of Probation (During the second year the community service must be completed within the first 10 months)
Costs: $268.00 (to be paid at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing the third month of Probation)
DNA Surcharge: $250.00 (to be paid through payment plan for costs)
Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
